commit.message:
Update recursion test

The recursion test included shellcode that was associated with the WannaCry ransomware attack. This shellcode has been removed and replaced with a different script that also covers the recursion.

Additionally, the previous recursion test was not run - this is also fixed.

commit.message:
Changes variables async and await to isAsync and awaitAllowed to conform with python 3.7

They have become reserved keywords
Added Donate button

Stable version 4.0.0

https://github.com/jquery/esprima at c0dfa42da4da9fa242dac623278a082cb38edc20

Make ReprVisitor return a string instead of bytes

There are string objects mixing with bytes formating in the ReprVisitor,
which raise exceptions whenever the user tries to print an object
(this is an issue only on Python3).

Either convert everything to bytes or to str before manipulating it.
Fix json tests for regex adding 'value: {}'

Fix parsing async get/set in a class

Fixes #1861
Fixes #1875
Closes gh-1939

Commit https://github.com/jquery/esprima/commit/c0dfa42da4da9fa242dac623278a082cb38edc20

Recognize Token.StringLiteral as a ReturnStatement argument.

This fix is similar to the one from #1882 for Token.Template.

Fixes #1897
Fixes #1928
Closes gh-1925

Commit https://github.com/jquery/esprima/commit/39e7668d8262eff129a52c416e9b9be4e811bdf5

Update TypeScript compiler, linter, and formatter to the latest version

Some formatting tweaks and identifier renaming (to adhere to the
variable unshadowing rule) are necessary.

Closes gh-1906

Commit https://github.com/jquery/esprima/commit/a04bcec80bf9d01330e83ff69bee8bf8424c59a3

Make the pure tokenizer a bit aggressive in recognizing regex literals.

At the same time, ensure that it can fall back if the regex literal
proved to be invalid.

Fix #1772
Fix #1873
Close gh-1889

Correct the handling of HTML comment when parsing as a module

Fix #1841

Commit https://github.com/jquery/esprima/commit/512ce40c276c53adadb5f87e992c91b94bad614d

Recognize Token.Template as a ReturnStatement argument.

When a Template is broken across multiple lines, the existing hasArgument test fails.
The Template is scanned as a single token so we just need to check for it after the return.

Fixes #1829
Closes gh-1882

Test fixture: move an async test to the more proper location.
